<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <title>Region: Obelisk</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://the-void-plane.neocities.org/style.css">
    <script src="https://the-void-plane.neocities.org/script.js"></script>
  </head>
  <body class="obelisk">
    <div class="page-div">
      <h1 class="typewriter">Region: Obelisk</h1>
      <p class="typewriter">The region Obelisk resembles a large sprawling highway system. These roads are not fixed to ground level, being able to tunnel under or bridging over other roads. They usually have four lanes or less, but can have more than that. There is no clear limit to how far highways can stack. Sometimes creating looming structures of stacks over four. Where there is no road present, a thick layer of white sand can be found.<br>
      <br>
      The roads are lit by bright sodium lights that pierce the region's dark grey mist. The mist feels thick, but allows for extremely far vision, which makes the stacked road structures of the region visible. Even with no direct heat source present, the temperature of this region rests at around 30 degrees Celsius, but cools down when further away from the ground level.<br>
      <br>
      The highways can also have road signs placed on the side or on an overpass. These are illegible however, as they have the <a href="https://the-void-plane.neocities.org/other/babel-effect.html" class="archive-link">Babel Effect</a> placed on them. To exit this region, gateways are alost always present in road tunnels, taking the shape of emergency exit doors.</p>
      </div>
      <a href="https://the-void-plane.neocities.org/archive/regions.html" class="button-return">
        <div class="return-icon"></div>
        <p>Return to Regions</p>
      </a>
  </body>
</html>
